                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/49.</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Official statement of Haitian Government, published in Le
                        Moniteur of January 25, 1911.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head"
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1911-01-25">January 25, 1911</date>]</dateline>
                <p rend="right">
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State for Foreign Relations</hi>
                    </placeName>.</p>
                <p>The Government, faithful in its duty of informing the people concerning the
                    incident at Pedernales, advises that its commissioners returned on the 19th of
                    this month without having been able to settle amicably the dispute existing
                    between the two Republics. There has <pb facs="0236" n="154" xml:id="pg_154"/>
                    been drawn up by the commissioners of the two States the following report,<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d173fn1">Not printed.</note> which brings their mission to an
                    end, and by which they have declared that they leave the matter to the decision
                    of their respective Governments.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
